{"name":"Memory of the Dragon","type":"item","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/lizard-single-slit-pink.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","description":"You have discovered the truth about Saint George's past—that his friendship with the Dragon was real, that the plague was orchestrated, and that the entire tragedy was manipulated by the One Who Plots in the Shadows. This terrible knowledge has awakened something within you: the memory of the Dragon's perspective. Once per Session, you can spend 2 Soma to access the Dragon's ancient wisdom. For the rest of the Scene, you gain the Descriptor **'I remember what the Dragon knew about ancient laws and betrayals.'** This grants you knowledge about: the true nature of binding oaths and ancient laws, how to recognize manipulation by the One Who Plots, the history of conflict between humans and magical creatures, and ways to resist corruption. Additionally, while this Descriptor is active, Saint George (if present) will become visibly shaken when you speak with the Dragon's wisdom, reducing his Opposition Level by 1 as his resolve wavers with painful memories.","somaCost":2,"requirement":"Investigate Saint George's background thoroughly and discover concrete evidence that his entire story was orchestrated—the unnatural plague, the mysterious benefactor who funded his training, and the ancient laws that truly bound the Dragon.","scenario":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","notes":"This is the most powerful and narrative Gift from this scenario. The 2 Soma cost reflects the emotional and mental weight of channeling the Dragon's memories. The Descriptor is deliberately open-ended, allowing creative use: convincing Saint George of his manipulation, understanding how ancient oaths work, recognizing other victims of the One Who Plots, or resisting similar corruption. The effect on Saint George (reduce OL by 1 when you speak with Dragon's wisdom) is crucial for his redemption arc—hearing his friend's voice through the Hunter forces him to confront what he did. This Gift essentially gives Hunters access to a deceased NPC's knowledge, making it invaluable for the campaign's larger mystery. The Storyteller should roleplay moments where the Hunter's eyes change, their voice deepens, and they speak with ancient authority when invoking this Gift. If used skillfully, this Gift can completely redeem Saint George and turn him into the most valuable ally against the One Who Plots in the Shadows."},"_id":"806401511780acb0"}
{"name":"Paladin's Oath","type":"item","img":"icons/magic/holy/chalice-glowing-gold-water.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","description":"You have earned the respect of one of Saint George's Paladins through your actions, and they have shared with you the sacred oath that binds them to their cause. Choose one of the six Paladins you encountered. You gain insight into their special ability and can invoke their spirit once per Scene to aid you. **Trebizond** (create exotic equipment Descriptor, +1 OL when using it), **Demetrius** (take 1 Wound for ally, +1 OL rest of Scene), **Theodore** (inflict 1 Additional Wound when raging, or 1 Wound even on successful Defense), **Martha** (enemies get 2 Penalties when targeting you if other allies present), **Syrus** (negate one Hunter Gift effect per Scene), or **Margaret** (gain +1 OL for each Wound Saint George has suffered). You can only invoke the chosen Paladin's power once per Scene, and it lasts for a single action. The Paladin you choose reflects your own values and fighting style.","somaCost":1,"requirement":"Defeat or befriend one of Saint George's Paladins during a Witch Hunt, learning their Downside and recognizing their humanity despite being on opposite sides.","scenario":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","notes":"This Gift represents forming a bond with one of the Paladins, recognizing that they are not monsters but warriors bound by duty and loyalty. The 1 Soma cost represents channeling their spirit for aid. Each Paladin offers a different tactical option: Trebizond for versatility, Demetrius for protection, Theodore for offense, Martha for defense, Syrus for control, Margaret for power scaling. The Storyteller should roleplay the chosen Paladin's spirit appearing briefly to assist—perhaps offering advice, manifesting as an aura, or their voice encouraging the Hunter. Martha is the most likely to secretly help Hunters during a Witch Hunt, as her Downside shows she believes Broken Tales should be understood, not eradicated. If Saint George is redeemed, the Paladin you bonded with may become a recurring ally NPC."},"_id":"881377986cfeaa89"}
{"name":"The Saint's Blessing","type":"item","img":"icons/magic/holy/angel-winged-humanoid-blue.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","description":"Saint George has recognized your good intentions and blessed you with a fragment of his holy power. Once per Scene, when you would suffer a Wound from a creature with monstrous, magical, or supernatural Descriptors, you can invoke the Saint's protection to reduce the damage. Roll 1 die: on a result of 4-6, you completely avoid the Wound; on 1-3, you still suffer it but gain 1 Additional Success on your next action against that creature. Additionally, you get 1 Additional Success on all Defense Checks against attacks from Dark Presences who serve the One Who Plots in the Shadows, as Saint George's blessing reveals their true nature.","somaCost":0,"requirement":"Accumulate enough Judgment Tokens to prove your good intentions to Saint George, causing him to end any Witch Hunt and become a permanent ally.","scenario":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","notes":"This Gift represents Saint George's acknowledgment that the Hunters are true heroes, not monsters. The 1 die roll (4-6 avoids Wound, 1-3 suffers but gets +1 next action) reflects the unpredictable nature of divine protection. The bonus against servants of the One Who Plots connects to Saint George's own manipulation—his blessing helps Hunters recognize and resist similar corruption. Saint George must have transitioned from Witch Hunt mode back to ally status for this Gift to be acquired. Once received, this Gift symbolizes Saint George's permanent trust and can even help him eventually discover his own manipulated past if Hunters share what they learn about the One Who Plots in the Shadows."},"_id":"356d7f4f8beb91d8"}